{"title":"Alberto Mariola, PhD","markdown":{"yaml":{"title":"Alberto Mariola, PhD","image":"avatar.jpg","about":{"template":"trestles","image-shape":"round","links":[{"icon":"twitter","href":"https://twitter.com/langestroop"},{"icon":"linkedin","href":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/alberto-mariola-449b91160/"},{"icon":"github","href":"https://github.com/langestroop"},{"text":"{{< ai google-scholar >}}","href":"https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=93msY9YAAAAJ&hl=it&oi=ao"},{"text":"{{< ai researchgate >}}","href":"https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Alberto-Mariola-2?ev=hdr_xprf"}]}},"containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n\n:::{#hero-heading}\n\nI am a Postdoctoral Research Fellow working at the University of Sussex (UK) in the [Episodic Memory Group](http://www.sussex.ac.uk/psychology/memory/index) with Prof [Chris Bird](https://scholar.google.co.uk/citations?user=smxv3nIAAAAJ&hl=en).\n\nMy work lies at the intersection of human perception, memory and metacognition. Specifically, I am interested in the neural and computational mechanisms that underlie event segmentation, namely humansâ€™ ability to segment the continuous flow of information reaching their senses into units of experience and how this ability influences memory and reality monitoring. To do so, I am mostly employing a combination of naturalistic experimental paradigms (e.g., videos, movies, XR technologies), neuroimaging (e.g., M/EEG combined with eye tracking) and computational modelling.\n\nThis website is under construction, but feel free to reach out to me via [mail](mailto:a.mariola@protonmail.ch) and/or via any of the included reported social media platform links \n\n:::"},"formats":{"html":{"execute":{"fig-width":7,"fig-height":5,"fig-format":"retina","fig-dpi":96,"df-print":"default","error":false,"eval":true,"cache":null,"freeze":false,"echo":true,"output":true,"warning":true,"include":true,"keep-md":false,"keep-ipynb":false,"ipynb":null,"enabled":null,"daemon":null,"daemon-restart":false,"de